<p><br>
When the parallelogram is specified from the lengths <i>B</i> and <i>C</i> =
of two adjacent sides together with the length <i>D</i><sub>1</sub> of eith=
er diagonal, then the area can be found from <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedi=
a.org/wiki/Heron%27s_formula" title=3D"Heron's formula">Heron's formula</a>=
. Specifically it is
</p>
<dl><dd><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span clas=
s=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyl=
e K=3D2{\sqrt {S(S-B)(S-C)(S-D_{1})}}=3D{\frac {1}{2}}{\sqrt {(B+C+D_{1})(-=
B+C+D_{1})(B-C+D_{1})(B+C-D_{1})}},}">
