<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading2"><h2 id=3D"Proof_that_diagonals_bisect=
_each_other">Proof that diagonals bisect each other</h2><span class=3D"mw-e=
ditsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https=
://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DParallelogram&amp;action=3Dedit&amp=
;section=3D6" title=3D"Edit section: Proof that diagonals bisect each other=
"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></spa=
n></div>
<figure class=3D"mw-default-size mw-halign-right" typeof=3D"mw:File"><a hre=
f=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Parallelogram1.svg" class=3D"mw-fil=
e-description" title=3D"Parallelogram ABCD"><img alt=3D"Parallelogram ABCD"=
 src=3D"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/9e/Parallelo=
gram1.svg/250px-Parallelogram1.svg.png" decoding=3D"async" width=3D"200" he=
ight=3D"150" class=3D"mw-file-element" data-file-width=3D"200" data-file-he=
ight=3D"150"></a><figcaption>Parallelogram ABCD</figcaption></figure>
<p>To prove that the diagonals of a parallelogram bisect each other, we wil=
l use <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Congruence_(geometry)" title=
=3D"Congruence (geometry)">congruent</a> <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.or=
g/wiki/Triangle#Basic_facts" title=3D"Triangle">triangles</a>:
</p>
<dl><dd><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span clas=
s=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyl=
e \angle ABE\cong \angle CDE}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mi mathvariant=3D"normal">=E2=88=A0<!-- =E2=88=A0 --></mi>
        <mi>A</mi>
        <mi>B</mi>
        <mi>E</mi>
        <mo>=E2=89=85<!-- =E2=89=85 --></mo>
        <mi mathvariant=3D"normal">=E2=88=A0<!-- =E2=88=A0 --></mi>
        <mi>C</mi>
        <mi>D</mi>
        <mi>E</mi>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle \angle ABE\co=
ng \angle CDE}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/fab9e09a52dea0bf091179212defbbf6035ff086" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -0.338ex; width:17.204ex; height:2.176ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle \a=
ngle ABE\cong \angle CDE}"></span> <i>(alternate interior angles are equal =
in measure)</i></dd>
<dd><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class=3D=
"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><mat=
h xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyle \a=
ngle BAE\cong \angle DCE}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mi mathvariant=3D"normal">=E2=88=A0<!-- =E2=88=A0 --></mi>
        <mi>B</mi>
        <mi>A</mi>
        <mi>E</mi>
        <mo>=E2=89=85<!-- =E2=89=85 --></mo>
        <mi mathvariant=3D"normal">=E2=88=A0<!-- =E2=88=A0 --></mi>
        <mi>D</mi>
        <mi>C</mi>
        <mi>E</mi>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle \angle BAE\co=
ng \angle DCE}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/f6807434bee15ed8506eb916def45f584f398fb0" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -0.338ex; width:17.204ex; height:2.176ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle \a=
ngle BAE\cong \angle DCE}"></span> <i>(alternate interior angles are equal =
in measure)</i>.</dd></dl>
<p>(since these are angles that a transversal makes with <a href=3D"https:/=
/en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Parallel_(geometry)" title=3D"Parallel (geometry)">p=
arallel lines</a> <i>AB</i> and <i>DC</i>).
</p><p>Also, side <i>AB</i> is equal in length to side <i>DC</i>, since opp=
osite sides of a parallelogram are equal in length.
</p><p>Therefore, triangles <i>ABE</i> and <i>CDE</i> are congruent (ASA po=
stulate, <i>two corresponding angles and the included side</i>).
</p><p>Therefore,
</p>
<dl><dd><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span clas=
s=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyl=
e AE=3DCE}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mi>A</mi>
        <mi>E</mi>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mi>C</mi>
        <mi>E</mi>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle AE=3DCE}</ann=
otation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/f6d80254dff1b2250ab27448227c0257efc43fe1" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -0.338ex; width:10.159ex; height:2.176ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle AE=
=3DCE}"></span></dd>
<dd><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class=3D=
"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><mat=
h xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyle BE=
=3DDE.}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mi>B</mi>
        <mi>E</mi>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mi>D</mi>
        <mi>E</mi>
        <mo>.</mo>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle BE=3DDE.}</an=
notation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/fff2cf29d8b7a94f92079ccca0cfbf611369228c" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -0.338ex; width:10.985ex; height:2.176ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle BE=
=3DDE.}"></span></dd></dl>
<p>Since the diagonals <i>AC</i> and <i>BD</i> divide each other into segme=
nts of equal length, the diagonals bisect each other.
</p><p>Separately, since the diagonals <i>AC</i> and <i>BD</i> bisect each =
other at point <i>E</i>, point <i>E</i> is the midpoint of each diagonal.
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading2"><h2 id=3D"Lattice_of_parallelograms">=
Lattice of parallelograms</h2><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D=
